				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The master clock always runs at 1890/88 = 21.47{72}MHz. The 5A22 contains (among other things) the 65c816 CPU and an address decoder, which translates the 65c816's bus address into SNES bus addresses, and determines the memory map region. The clock signal for the internal 65c816 is then simply held for 6, 8 or 12 master clock cycles while the rest of the 5A22 (e.g. DMA controller) and the system continues.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

