					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In 6502 terms, the SNES's φ2 cycle is 3, 5, or 9 master clock cycles depending on the specific address accessed, while φ1 is always 3 master clock cycles.<br /><br />(Ridiculous exception: DMA access is actually φ1=φ2=4 master clock cycles)</div>

